025/**
026 *  Possible values for the SVG attribute
027 *  {@value org.tquadrat.foundation.svg.SVGUtils#SVGATTRIBUTE_PreserveAspectRatio}.

037@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: SVGPreserveAspectRatio.java 980 2022-01-06 15:29:19Z tquadrat $" )
038@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
039public enum SVGPreserveAspectRatio
040{
041        /*------------------*\
042    ====** Enum Declaration **=================================================
043        \*------------------*/
044    /**
045     *  Do not force uniform scaling. Scale the graphic content of the given
046     *  element non-uniformly if necessary such that the element's bounding box
047     *  exactly matches the viewport rectangle.
048     */
049    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
050    NONE( "none" ),
051
052    /**
053     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
054     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} of the element's viewBox with the
055     *  smallest x type of the viewport.<br>
056     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} of the element's viewBox with the
057     *  smallest y type of the viewport.
058     */
059    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
060    XMIN_YMIN( "xMinYMin" ),
061
062    /**
063     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
064     *  <br>Align the midpoint x type of the element's viewBox with the
065     *  midpoint x type of the viewport.<br>
066     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} of the element's viewBox with the
067     *  smallest y type of the viewport.
068     */
069    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
070    XMID_YMIN( "xMidYMin" ),
071
072    /**
073     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
074     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} +{@code <width>} of the element's viewBox
075     *  with the maximum x type of the viewport.<br>
076     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} of the element's viewBox with the
077     *  smallest y type of the viewport.
078     */
079    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
080    XMAX_YMIN( "xMaxYMin" ),
081
082    /**
083     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
084     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} of the element's viewBox with the
085     *  smallest x type of the viewport.<br>
086     *  <br>Align the midpoint y type of the element's viewBox with the
087     *  midpoint y type of the viewport.
088     */
089    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
090    XMIN_YMID( "xMinYMid" ),
091
092    /**
093     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
094     *  <br>Align the midpoint x type of the element's viewBox with the
095     *  midpoint x type of the viewport.<br>
096     *  <br>Align the midpoint y type of the element's viewBox with the
097     *  midpoint y type of the viewport.<br>
098     *  <br>This is the default setting.
099     */
100    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
101    XMID_YMID( "xMidYMid" ),
102
103    /**
104     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
105     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} + {@code <width>} of the element's
106     *  viewBox with the maximum x type of the viewport.<br>
107     *  <br>Align the midpoint y type of the element's viewBox with the
108     *  midpoint y type of the viewport.
109     */
110    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
111    XMAX_YMID( "xMaxYMid" ),
112
113    /**
114     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
115     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} of the element's viewBox with the
116     *  smallest x type of the viewport.<br>
117     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} + {@code <height>} of the element's
118     *  viewBox with the maximum y type of the viewport.
119     */
120    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
121    XMIN_YMAX( "xMinYMax" ),
122
123    /**
124     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
125     *  <br>Align the midpoint x type of the element's viewBox with the
126     *  midpoint x type of the viewport.<br>
127     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} + {@code <height>} of the element's
128     *  viewBox with the maximum y type of the viewport.
129     */
130    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
131    XMID_YMAX( "xMidYMax" ),
132
133    /**
134     *  Force uniform scaling.<br>
135     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-x>} + {@code <width>} of the element's
136     *  viewBox with the maximum x type of the viewport.<br>
137     *  <br>Align the {@code <min-y>} + {@code <height>} of the element's
138     *  viewBox with the maximum y type of the viewport.
139     */
140    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
141    XMAX_YMAX( "xMaxYMax" );
142

172}
